  "Raad van Bestuur is aimed at organizations that want to bring together board information, documents, and context faster for better decision-making.": "Board of Directors is aimed at organizations that want to bring together board information, documents, and context faster for better decision-making.",
  "Raad van Bestuur is gericht op organisaties die bestuursinformatie, documenten en context sneller willen samenbrengen voor betere besluitvorming.": "Board of Directors is aimed at organizations that want to bring together governance information, documents and context faster for better decision-making.",
  "RAG does not magically make AI error-free. You still need good source data, logical document structure and a solid search layer to get reliable answers.": "RAG does not magically make AI error-free. You still need good source data, logical document structure and a solid search layer to get reliable answers.",
  "RAG is a way for a language model to retrieve relevant information first before answering.": "RAG is a way for a language model to retrieve relevant information first before answering.",
  "RAG is een manier om een taalmodel eerst relevante informatie op te laten halen voordat het antwoord geeft.": "RAG is a way for a language model to retrieve relevant information first before answering.",
  "RAG maakt AI niet magisch foutloos. Je hebt nog steeds goede brondata, logische documentstructuur en een degelijke zoeklaag nodig om betrouwbare antwoorden te krijgen.": "RAG does not magically make AI error-free. You still need good source data, logical document structure and a solid search layer to get reliable answers.",
  "RAG staat voor Retrieval-Augmented Generation. Eerst wordt relevante informatie opgehaald uit documenten of een kennisbank, daarna gebruikt het model die informatie om een beter antwoord te geven.": "RAG stands for Retrieval-Augmented Generation. First, relevant information is retrieved from documents or a knowledge base, then the model uses that information to provide a better answer.",
  "RAG stands for Retrieval-Augmented Generation. First, relevant information is retrieved from documents or a knowledge base, then the model uses that information to provide a better answer.": "RAG stands for Retrieval-Augmented Generation. First, relevant information is retrieved from documents or a knowledge base, then the model uses that information to provide a better answer.",
